    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        Heater
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x0824101" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Heater</title>
        <table id="t0824102" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Heater</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.73in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.28in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F19 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F19. Move key switch to ignition position and at F19 and circuit 12B,
                                measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F19, 12B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (36) and move key switch to ignition position. At conn. (36),
                                measure voltage from circuit 75A to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(36), 75A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower switch (36) by placing it in low position and measuring resistance
                                from B to E.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (36), term. B to E.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower switch (36) by placing it in medium position and measuring
                                resistance from A to E.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (36), term. A to E.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower switch (36) by placing it in high position and measuring resistance
                                from C to E.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (36), term. C to E.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove relay (73) and disconnect connector (44). Reconnect connector switch (36) and
                                set blower control switch to low speed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch to ignition position and at connector (44), measure voltage from
                                circuit 75D to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(44), 75D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move blower switch to medium speed and at conn. (44), measure voltage from circuit 75C
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(44), 75C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move blower switch to high speed and at conn. (73), measure voltage from circuit 75B
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(73), 75B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower motor resistor by measuring resistance from terminal 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Resistor, term. 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Approx. 0 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace resistor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower motor resistor by measuring resistance from terminal 2 to 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Resistor, term. 2 to 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Approx. .35 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace resistor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test blower motor resistor by measuring resistance from terminal 3 to 4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Resistor, term. 3 to 4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Approx. 1.2 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace resistor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (44), move key switch to ignition position and blower switch to medium
                                position. At (73) measure voltage at circuit 75E to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(73), 75E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With ignition and blower switches still on, at (73) measure voltage from circuit 75E
                                to 75-GA.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(73), 75E to 75-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GA/ 11-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove fuse F12 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F12</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Re-install F12 and at F12 and circuit 14B, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F12, 14B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (73), measure voltage from circuit 75 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(73), 75 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Bench test relay (73) by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(73), 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Bench test relay (73) by applying +12 volts to terminal 85 and ground to terminal 86.
                                Measure resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Energized relay (73), term. 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Re-install relay (73) and disconnect connector (210). Move key switch to ignition
                                position and blower switch to high. At (210) measure voltage from circuit 75F to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(210), 75F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With key switch and blower switch still on, at (210) measure voltage from circuit 75F
                                to 75-G.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(210), 75F to 75-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-G, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Reconnect (210). Move key switch to ignition position. Does blower function
                                properly?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Blower circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace blower motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
